cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with information theoretic aspects of secure communication over a broadcast erasure channel with state feedback. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with security and cryptography, which suggests categories such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of linear complexity two-phase schemes, which suggests categories such as cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
